<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Walolen</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-03-25 12:49:35</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>It's not that the root doesn't hold on the EBS so much as it is that you and your party tend to ruin the root effect.  Ensnaring roots will hold up to around 2 minutes under ideal circumstances, but the problem here is that folks think root spells are meant for stopping runners - and they're not.  Root spells are meant to keep things in one place till you're ready to deal with it (kinda like mezmerizing spells and charm).  Snares are meant for stopping runners - it's that simple.  Try using an EBS the RIGHT way - start soloing something outdoors and when it procs, you back off and heal/blast/arrow your target until the root breaks - key being that you stop attacking with melee when the root procs and you'll see what I mean.  Whenever my blade proc'ed in fights, it was almost never effective at stopping runners, but when it proc'ed when I ran out of arrows and got lazy, I'd have time to empty DOT's and tons of arrows into my target before the root broke.  The easiest solution to the snare breaking is to just have a wizard or two and let em know to blast runners rather than count on the melee types to finish.</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
