<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: norgoth</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-04-13 13:48:10</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Well Walolen described the use very well. You dont use the ebonies' procs "instead of" the snare. They are used for two different purposes. You can use the ebonies when you are not concerned about a runner and get the added benefit of the dmg done by ensnaring roots. However, when it does proc., step back and do some non-melee dmg(bow and dot). This will give you a chance to cast the stinging swarm on it. When roots breaks, do it again with your ebonies. However, if u are concerned about a runner, either dont use the ebonies or be prepared to use snare when the mob turns and runs for his buddies. If you are using the ebonies though make sure your group knows it so that if your ebonies proc and break snare, the group is there to kill the mob before it runs too far.</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Waybetter</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-04-16 16:23:56</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>EBS are useless weapons plain and simple.<BR>
<BR>
A normal fight goes like this: 4 mobs get pulled - Enchanter mezzes, all assist puller, ranger attempts snare right away in case of resist (with a good group snare can be cast on the mob right away because the mob is killed before it wears off), cleric heals, 1 mob down, ranger selects next target, all assist, snare, dead, remezz if necessary, rinse and repeat.<BR>
<BR>
With a ranger using EBS the fight goes like this (don't forget that in dungeons mobs can cast SOW on each other):4 mobs get pulled - Enchanter mezzes, all assist puller, ranger snares, cleric heals, EBS procs and snare broken, next hit from the warrior causes root to break, mob goes tearing off out door and down hallway, all the fighters run after it leaving Cleric and enchanter in room with 3 mobs, Mezz breaks, enchanter yells '2 on me' and there is no one there to taunt, 2 of the fighters peel off from chasing runner and head back to room, 1 fighter stays on runner and eventually kills him, fighters taunt off mob, mezz recast, things seem under control, remaining fighter comes back from chase bringing 4 friends who all go agro on the enchanter, enchanter goes down, cleric goes down from agroing because of heals, 2 fighters take a beating, ranger yells "TRAIN TO ZONE" an runs for it.<BR>
<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: GreyWidget</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-04-21 18:51:14</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I have been dual wielding 2 of these for a couple of levels now and they are great. The Ensnaring Roots Proc, like the spell, seems to last 0, 30, 60 or 90 secs. It is much easier to know when you can recast a snare now that Verant have added the "Your Ensnaring Roots has worn off" message. The only time I consider putting these away is when snaring and blasting HGs or IGs as they can do some serious damage to the part before you get another snare on. Also, if the Ensnaring roots proc holds, you can step back and practice your archery for a bit ) </font></td></tr></table>
